metadata.name: Darkness Within
metadata.description:
“How can I be substantial if I do not cast a shadow? I must have a dark side also if I am to be whole.” 
-Carl Jung

Once we allow ourselves to recognize and accept the darkness that exists within us, we are able to see ourselves more clearly. We can become more grounded, whole, and capable of honest and real connection. Our relationship with ourselves and others improve, and our minds and hearts are open to greater compassion and understanding. 

This 1/1 piece was generated using Stable Diffusion AI, upscaled and enhanced and hand-painted in Photoshop. The final image is 4800x6000 pixels and printable as a 16x20in portrait.
